Name: Rccb
Specifications: Amperage: 40A ; Poles: FP ; Breaking Capacity: 10kA ; Sensitivity: 100mA
Key_Features: Larger Terminal Size , Real Trip Indicator , Test Button For Device Health , Lockable Knob , Air Flow Channels , Functionally independent of line voltage , Bus-Bar/Cable Termination on both sides , Line Load Reversibility convenient for termination , Load identification facility provided by Label Holder , Terminal equipped with shutter to avoid chances of wrong entry of wire during the installation for safety , IS/IEC Certified
Full_Description: Polycab RCCB (Residual Current Circuit Breaker), is an electrical safety device used to protect against electric shock and prevent electrical fires caused by ground faults and leakage currents
Short_Description: Protection against leakage current & earth faults
